<recipeml version="0.5">
  <recipe>
    <head>
      <title>Basic Cookie Mix</title>
      <categories>
        <cat>Master mix</cat></categories>
      <yield>1</yield></head>
    <ingredients>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>8</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Unbleached Flour</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Brown Sugar, Firmly Packed</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1 1/2</qty>
          <unit>teaspoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Baking Soda</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2 1/2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Granulated Sugar</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>4</qty>
          <unit>teaspoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Salt</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>3</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Vegetable Shortening</item></ing></ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>  Sift dry ingredients together into a large bowl, mixing well.  With a
  pastry blender, cut shotening into dry ingredients until evenly
  distributed.  Put into a large airtight container and label as Basic Cookie
  mix.  Store in a cool dry place and use within 10 to 12 weeks.
  
  Makes about 16 cups of mix.
  From "Make-A-Mix Cookery" by Karine Eliason, Nevada Harward &amp; Madeline
  Westover via The Home BBS. Posted to MM-Recipes Digest #336, 9 Dec 96 by
  c.simpson@worldnet.att.net
 
</step></directions></recipe></recipeml>
